  • Classes in fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.simulators.interfaces used by fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.simulators 
    Class and Description
    RTAtomicSimulatorI
    The class RTAtomicSimulatorI defines the core behaviour of atomic simulation engines that execute models using the physical clock (of the underlying computer) as simulation clock, or a linear transformation of it (to simulate either faster or slower than the real physical time).
    RTSchedulingI
    The interface RTSchedulerI declares the real time scheduler interface used in this library to execute simulation tasks in real time simulation engine.
    RTSimulatorI
    The interface RTSimulationI defines the core behaviour of simulation engines that execute models using the physical clock (of the underlying computer) as simulation clock, or a linear transformation of it (to simulate either faster or slower than the real physical time).
    SimulationManagementI
    The interface SimulationManagementI declares the methods used by simulation engines to manage simulation runs.
    SimulatorI
    The interface SimulationI declares the core behaviour of DEVS simulation engines.
